.TH manta-power-off-group 1  "group " 
.SH NAME
manta\-power\-off\-group \- Power off all nodes in a group
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBmanta power off group\fR [\fB\-g\fR|\fB\-\-graceful\fR] [\fB\-R\fR|\fB\-\-reason\fR] [\fB\-y\fR|\fB\-\-assume\-yes\fR] [\fB\-\-no\-wait\fR] [\fB\-o\fR|\fB\-\-output\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fICLUSTER_NAME\fR> 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Power off all nodes in a group
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-g\fR, \fB\-\-graceful\fR
Perform a graceful shutdown
.TP
\fB\-R\fR, \fB\-\-reason\fR \fI<TEXT>\fR
Reason for the power operation
.TP
\fB\-y\fR, \fB\-\-assume\-yes\fR
Skip confirmation prompts
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-wait\fR
Return as soon as the transition is queued; don\*(Aqt poll for completion
.TP
\fB\-o\fR, \fB\-\-output\fR \fI<FORMAT>\fR [default: table]
Output format
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
table
.IP \(bu 2
json
.RE
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.TP
<\fICLUSTER_NAME\fR>
Group name
